cherry_picks:
  # Commits we cherry-picked from beyond the pinned next-branch SHA.
  - sha: 8d65b60525f54258ec4ab381b4c7f80ec94148c5
    subject: "h700/u-boot: lpddr3 config"
    rationale: |
      Adds support for the LPDDR3 DRAM variant of the Anbernic RG35XX
      Pro alongside the more common LPDDR4 variant. Bumps U-Boot to
      v2026.01 and replaces the legacy single defconfig with two
      DRAM-variant-specific defconfigs (lpddr3, lpddr4). Includes a
      DRAM controller fix for LPDDR3 timing parameter extraction.

  # The 4 base H700 DTBs (rg35xx-2024, rg35xx-h, rg35xx-plus, rg35xx-sp
  # without panel-revision suffix) are not separately imported; they
  # exist in upstream Linux 7.0.1's arch/arm64/boot/dts/allwinner/ and
  # are added via BR2_LINUX_KERNEL_INTREE_DTS_NAME so Buildroot compiles
  # them.

# defconfig-name file is no longer authoritative — each board picks its
# own U-Boot defconfig in board/<vendor>/<device>/defconfig.fragment.
